description:
Known for their visionary approach to design, Fernando and Humberto Campana combine leading-edge technology with Louis Vuitton’s leathercraft heritage in their Cocoon for the Objets Nomades collection. Its delicately perforated fiberglass shell is lined with calfskin, smooth on the outside and quilted on the inside. Specially-shaped cushions make this seat a coddling, enveloping retreat, the perfect place to laze the day away.

Detailed Features

79.5 x 135 x 82 cm  (Depth x Height x Width)

  • H 135 x W 82 x D 79.5 cm

  • Weight: 28 kg

  • Lagoon

  • Fiberglass shell covered with calfskin

  • Woolen cushions

  • 2-meter suspension cord covered in woven calfskin

  • Brass trim

  • Cord and edges in blue calfskin

  • Max. capacity: 100 kg

  • Limited edition of 30 per color

name: SWELL WAVE SUSPENDED BY ANDREW KUDLESS
description:
From the ingenious mind of designer Andrew Kudless comes the Swell Wave Suspended, a dynamic shelved structure that attaches to the wall to replicate waves undulating against a rock. Polished-oak shelves are connected by straps crafted from the House's leather. A striking symbol of art, movement and discovery, this piece epitomizes the free-spiritedness of Louis Vuitton's rich travel heritage.

Detailed Features

140 x 150 x 34 cm  (Depth x Height x Width)

  • H 53.1 x W 59.1 x L 13.8 inches/H 135 x W 150 x L 35 cm

  • Weight: 55.1 pounds/25 kg

  • Cream

  • 30% oak, 20% leather, 20% aluminum, 10% metal

  • Suspended by two wall attachments

  • Maximum load: 220.5 pounds/100 kg

  • For indoor use only
